About time! We've been waiting for ya!

153
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:15,020
Hope you guys been practicing!

154
00:11:26,340 --> 00:11:29,120
So, Inspector, what are you looking up in that dictionary?

155
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,320
Translating Czech.

156
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,240
Czech, huh?

157
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:35,780
So, does it have something to do with that investigation you've got going?

158
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:36,240
No.

159
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:38,140
It's a personal project.

160
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:42,400
I'm kind of surprised to see you're doing anything that's not related to your case.

161
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:43,980
It's from a picture book.

162
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,620
I like the illustration.

163
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:48,980
I just wanted to know what the passage said

164
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:53,380
Inspectors reading a picture book. That's something you don't see every day

165
